PRIVACY POLICY

This Privacy Policy ("Policy") describes how Silvaroc Studios L.L.C ("Silvaroc Studios," "we," "us," or "our") collects, uses, and protects personal information obtained from users ("User" or "you") when you use our software or services ("Software"). By accessing or using the Software, you consent to the practices described in this Policy. 

1. Information Collection:

a. Personal Information: We may collect personal information that you provide to us voluntarily, such as your name, email address, and other contact details, when you register an account or communicate with us.

b. Usage Data: We may automatically collect certain information about your use of the Software, including your IP address, device information, operating system, and usage patterns. This information is collected using cookies, beacons, and similar technologies.

c. Third-Party Sources: We may collect information about you from third-party sources, such as social media platforms, if you choose to link your account or interact with our Software through such platforms.

2. Use of Information:

a. We may use the personal information we collect to:
   i. Provide and improve our Software, including customizing your experience and responding to your inquiries and support requests.
   ii. Send you administrative notifications, updates, and marketing communications (with your consent, where required by applicable law).
   iii. Analyze usage patterns and trends to enhance the functionality and performance of our Software.
   iv. Prevent fraud, enforce our terms and conditions, and protect the rights, property, or safety of Silvaroc Studios and our users.

b. We may aggregate and anonymize data collected from you for statistical and analytical purposes, which may be shared with third parties.

3. Data Sharing:

a. We may share your personal information with third parties in the following cases:
   i. Service Providers: We may engage trusted third-party service providers to assist us in delivering our Software and related services. These providers are bound by confidentiality agreements and are only authorized to use your personal information as necessary to perform the services on our behalf.
   ii. Legal Compliance: We may disclose your personal information to comply with applicable laws, regulations, legal processes, or government requests.
   iii. Business Transfers: In the event of a merger, acquisition, or sale of all or a portion of our assets, your personal information may be transferred to the acquiring entity.

b. We will not sell, rent, or lease your personal information to third parties for their marketing purposes without your explicit consent.

4. Data Security:

a. Silvaroc Studios implements reasonable security measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction. However, no method of transmission over the internet or electronic storage is completely secure, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.

b. You are responsible for maintaining the confidentiality of your account credentials and for any actions taken under your account. Please notify us immediately if you suspect any unauthorized access to or use of your account.

5. Data Retention:

We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

6. Children's Privacy:

The Software is not intended for use by individuals under the age of 13. We do not knowingly collect personal information from children under 13. If we become aware that we have inadvertently collected personal information from a child under 13, we will take reasonable measures to delete such information from our systems.

7. Third-Party Links and Services:

Our Software may contain links to third-party websites or services that are not controlled or operated by Silvaroc Studios. This Policy does not apply to those third-party platforms. We encourage you to review the privacy policies of those

 third parties before providing any personal information.

8. Your Rights:

a. You have the right to access, update, and correct your personal information held by Silvaroc Studios. You may also request the deletion of your personal information, subject to applicable legal requirements.

b. To exercise your rights or make any inquiries regarding this Policy, please contact us using the information provided at the end of this document.

9. Changes to this Policy:

We may update this Policy from time to time. The revised Policy will be posted on our website or made available within the Software. By continuing to use the Software after the effective date of the revised Policy, you consent to the updated practices.

10. Contact Us:

